<Layout title="Answer Engine Optimisation (AEO) – UK Guide | Rank4AI" description="What is Answer Engine Optimisation? AEO explained for UK businesses. How to optimise for AI-generated answers.">
<section class="pt-12 pb-24 reveal">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'Learn', href: '/learn/' },
      { label: 'Guides', href: '/learn/guides/' },
      { label: 'Aeo' }
    ]} />

    <p class="section-tag">Guide</p>
    <h1 class="mb-6">Answer Engine Optimisation (AEO)</h1>

    <img src="/images/content/five-signal-model.svg" alt="The Five Signal Model for AI search" class="w-full rounded-xl mb-8 mt-6" loading="lazy">
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Answer Engine Optimisation (AEO) is the practice of optimising content so AI platforms can extract, summarise, and cite it when answering user questions. It is closely related to GEO (Generative Engine Optimisation) and AI SEO – all three terms describe the same fundamental challenge.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The distinction: AEO focuses specifically on structured answers. It is about making your content the answer that AI platforms select, not just content they can find.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">How AEO Differs from SEO</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">SEO optimises for search engine rankings. AEO optimises for AI-generated answers. In SEO, you aim for page 1. In AEO, you aim to be the answer itself – the business that gets named when someone asks AI a question.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Core AEO Principles</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 mb-10">
      <div class="card-teal-border"><h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">Answer the question directly</h3><p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Structure content around clear questions and provide clear, concise answers in the first 150 words.</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">Build entity authority</h3><p class="text-sm text-text-muted">AI platforms recommend entities they trust. Trust comes from consistent presence across multiple independent sources.</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">Use structured data</h3><p class="text-sm text-text-muted">FAQ schema, How-To schema, and Organisation schema help AI platforms extract and attribute your answers correctly.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>

    <!-- Internal links -->
